components.label: HTML
components.content: For new clients, ensure that the new client and other customer due diligence checklists (see PF1) have been fully completed and approved by the Responsible Individual.

components.label: HTML
components.content: For existing clients, consider the need to update customer due diligence procedures (eg. due to changes in ownership and control or other significant changes at the client or changes in the nature / extent of the services we provide to them) (see PF1).

components.label: HTML
components.content: Complete acceptance of appointment / reappointment form (see B12) to identify whether there are any actual or perceived Ethical Standard threats.

components.label: HTML
components.content: Complete / update the summary of the group (see PF1-5) and consider whether sufficient appropriate evidence can be expected to be obtained in relation to the consolidation process and financial information of components.

components.label: HTML
components.content: Consider whether it will be possible to have sufficient involvement with the component auditors (see PF1-9).
